.TH LIXPLORE 1 "December 2024" "lixplore 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lixplore \- Academic literature search and export tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lixplore
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lixplore
is a command-line tool for searching academic literature across multiple databases 
(PubMed, Crossref, DOAJ, EuropePMC, arXiv) and exporting results in various formats 
(CSV, Excel, JSON, BibTeX, RIS, EndNote, XML).

All exports are automatically organized into format-specific folders within the 
.I exports/
directory.

.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Source Selection"
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-pubmed
Search PubMed (biomedical and life sciences literature)
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-crossref
Search Crossref (scholarly works with DOIs)
.TP
.BR \-J ", " \-\-doaj
Search DOAJ (Directory of Open Access Journals)
.TP
.BR \-E ", " \-\-europepmc
Search EuropePMC (Europe PubMed Central)
.TP
.BR \-x ", " \-\-arxiv
Search arXiv (preprint repository for physics, math, CS, etc.)
.TP
.BR \-A ", " \-\-all
Search ALL sources at once
.TP
.BR \-s " \fICODES\fR, " \-\-sources " \fICODES\fR"
Combined source selection using codes: P=PubMed, C=Crossref, J=DOAJ, 
E=EuropePMC, X=arXiv, A=All
.br
Example: \fB-s PX\fR for PubMed+arXiv, \fB-s PCE\fR for PubMed+Crossref+EuropePMC

.SS "Search Parameters"
.TP
.BR \-q " \fITEXT\fR, " \-\-query " \fITEXT\fR"
Search query string. Supports Boolean operators for advanced queries:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBAND\fR - Both terms required (e.g., "cancer AND treatment")
.IP \(bu 2
\fBOR\fR - Either term (e.g., "cancer OR tumor")
.IP \(bu 2
\fBNOT\fR - Exclude term (e.g., "diabetes NOT type1")
.IP \(bu 2
\fBParentheses\fR - Group terms (e.g., "(cancer OR tumor) AND treatment")
.RE
.IP
Examples: \fB-q "cancer treatment"\fR | \fB-q "cancer AND treatment"\fR | \fB-q "(cancer OR tumor) AND treatment"\fR
.TP
.BR \-au " \fINAME\fR, " \-\-author " \fINAME\fR"
Search by author name
.br
Example: \fB-au "Smith J"\fR
.TP
.BR \-DOI " \fIDOI\fR, " \-\-doi " \fIDOI\fR"
Search for a specific article by DOI
.br
Example: \fB-DOI "10.1038/nature12345"\fR
.TP
.BR \-m " \fIN\fR, " \-\-max_results " \fIN\fR"
Maximum number of results to fetch per source (default: 10)
.br
Example: \fB-m 50\fR

.SS "Filtering & Processing"
.TP
.BR \-d " \fIFROM TO\fR, " \-\-date " \fIFROM TO\fR"
Filter by publication date range in YYYY-MM-DD format
.br
Example: \fB-d 2020-01-01 2024-12-31\fR
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-deduplicate
Remove duplicate results when searching multiple sources (recommended with \fB-A\fR or \fB-s\fR)
.TP
.BR \-\-sort " \fIORDER\fR"
Sort results by specified order. Options:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBrelevant\fR - Default, original API order (most relevant first)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBnewest\fR - Latest publications first (by year, descending)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBoldest\fR - Earliest publications first (by year, ascending)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBjournal\fR - Alphabetical by journal name
.IP \(bu 2
\fBauthor\fR - Alphabetical by first author's last name
.RE
.IP
Example: \fB--sort newest\fR

.SS "Display Options"
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-abstract
Display abstracts along with titles in the results
.TP
.BR \-N " \fIN\fR [\fIN\fR ...], " \-\-number " \fIN\fR [\fIN\fR ...]"
View detailed information for specific article(s) by number
.br
Example: \fB-N 1\fR or \fB-N 1 2 3\fR
.TP
.BR \-R " \fIN\fR [\fIN\fR ...], " \-\-review " \fIN\fR [\fIN\fR ...]"
Open article(s) in separate terminal window for detailed review. Works in two modes:
.br
1. Combined with search: \fB-P -q "query" -R 1 2 3\fR
.br
2. Standalone (from cached results): \fBlixplore -R 1 2 3\fR
.br
In the review window, press \fBq\fR or \fBCtrl+C\fR to close.
.br
Example: \fB-R 1\fR or \fB-R 1 2 3\fR
.TP
.BR \-st " \fIN\fR, " \-\-stat " \fIN\fR"
Get statistics for the specified count (default: 50)

.SS "Export & Output"
.TP
.BR \-X " \fIFORMAT\fR, " \-\-export " \fIFORMAT\fR"
Export results to specified format. Available formats:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBcsv\fR - CSV format (Excel, Google Sheets)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBxlsx\fR - Microsoft Excel format with formatting
.IP \(bu 2
\fBjson\fR - JSON structured data
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbibtex\fR - BibTeX format for LaTeX citations
.IP \(bu 2
\fBris\fR - RIS format (Zotero, Mendeley, RefWorks)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBenw\fR - EndNote Tagged format (recommended for EndNote)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBendnote\fR - EndNote XML format
.IP \(bu 2
\fBxml\fR - Generic XML format
.RE
.IP
Files are automatically saved to \fIexports/\fR folder
.TP
.BR \-o " \fIFILE\fR, " \-\-output " \fIFILE\fR"
Custom output filename for export (default: auto-generated with timestamp)
.br
Example: \fB-o my_results.csv\fR
.TP
.BR \-Z ", " \-\-zotero
Export results to Zotero reference manager

.SS "Utility"
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-history
Show search history
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Basic search:
.nf
lixplore -P -q "cancer treatment" -m 10
.fi
.TP
.B Multi-source search with export:
.nf
lixplore -s PX -q "machine learning" -m 20 -X xlsx -o ml_papers.xlsx
.fi
.TP
.B Search all sources with deduplication:
.nf
lixplore -A -q "COVID-19" -m 50 -D -X csv
.fi
.TP
.B Search with date filter and abstracts:
.nf
lixplore -P -q "diabetes" -d 2020-01-01 2024-12-31 -m 15 -a
.fi
.TP
.B Search by author:
.nf
lixplore -P -au "Smith J" -m 10 -a
.fi
.TP
.B Boolean operators in queries:
.nf
# AND operator (both terms required)
lixplore -P -q "cancer AND treatment" -m 10

# OR operator (either term)
lixplore -P -q "cancer OR tumor" -m 10

# NOT operator (exclude term)
lixplore -P -q "diabetes NOT type1" -m 10

# Complex query with parentheses
lixplore -P -q "(cancer OR tumor) AND (treatment OR therapy)" -m 20
.fi
.TP
.B Export to EndNote:
.nf
lixplore -P -q "neuroscience" -m 30 -X enw -o neuro_papers.enw
.fi
.TP
.B Review articles in separate terminal (two-step workflow):
.nf
# Step 1: Search and cache results
lixplore -P -q "paracetamol" -m 10

# Step 2: Review specific articles from cache
lixplore -R 1 5 9

# In review window: Press 'q' or Ctrl+C to close
.fi
.TP
.B Review during search (one-step):
.nf
lixplore -P -q "diabetes" -m 20 -R 1 3 5
.fi
.TP
.B Sort results and export selected:
.nf
# Get newest papers, export top 10
lixplore -P -q "cancer" -m 50 --sort newest -S first:10 -X xlsx

# Get oldest papers
lixplore -P -q "history" -m 50 --sort oldest -X csv
.fi
.TP
.B Smart selection patterns:
.nf
# Export odd-numbered articles
lixplore -P -q "research" -m 50 -S odd -X csv

# Export articles 10-20
lixplore -P -q "science" -m 50 -S 10-20 -X xlsx

# Export first 15 and last 5
lixplore -P -q "study" -m 50 -S first:15 last:5 -X enw
.fi

