.SH NOTES
When searching multiple sources, using the \fB-D\fR flag is recommended to remove 
duplicate results. The tool caches results for 7 days to improve performance on 
repeated searches.

.B Review Window Controls:
When using \fB-R\fR flag, articles open in separate terminal windows. To close a 
review window, press \fBq\fR (quit) or \fBCtrl+C\fR (interrupt). The window will 
not close with other keys, preventing accidental closes while reading.

.B Two-Step Review Workflow:
Search results are automatically cached, allowing you to review articles in a 
separate command without re-searching. This is useful for browsing titles first, 
then reviewing detailed information for selected articles.

For more detailed information and tutorials, visit the project documentation at:
